===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=psc|疒|疾|alt2=⿰大矢|c1=p|c2=p|t1=illness|t2=fast}}. The two characters, originally representing different words, have merged into one character representing both senses.

The oracle glyph of {{lang|zh|sc=Hani|⿰大矢}} depicts an arrow flying towards a person - "fast". The "illness" sense preserves the original meaning of {{och-l|*疒}}. The {{och-l|*亠}} component represents the person found in both pictograms.

===Etymology===
Perhaps from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-(t)sik|t=to burn, itch; angry}}, to which {{och-l|堲|coaled part of a burning torch}} has also been connected. Outside of Sinitic, compare {{cog|bo|ཚིག|t=to burn, glow, be inflamed}}, as well as perhaps {{cog|my|ချစ်|t=burnt}} (STEDT).

